codex
The program class itself does not use a class MBM in the header; `new Program(cfn)` is ordinary global `new`. In this codebase that still routes through the project `MemoryManager`, so address locality with MBM blocks is not proof of class ownership either. The only allocator-level proof is the first word looking like a freelist `next`, plus whether that address is on the shared size-0x50 allocator’s free list.
